definition.value: A fatty acid ethyl ester obtained by the formal condensation of  2-methylbutyric acid with ethanol. It is a constituent of the aroma of wines, strawberries, blueberries, and apples.
A methoxybenzoic acid that is benzoic acid substituted by a methoxy group at position 3.
A leukotriene composed of (6Z,8E,10E,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoic acid carrying (5S)- and (12R)-hydroxy substituents.
An N(6)-acyl-L-lysine derivative in which the acyl group is specified as gamma-glutamyl.
